    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="517"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.01/145</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Halifax</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-28">March 28,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Welles</hi>: On instructions from London I send you
                    herewith a copy of the text of the British Government’s proposals regarding <pb
                        facs="0634" n="622" xml:id="pg_622"/> India.<note n="38" xml:id="d517fn38"
                        >For text, see British Cmd. 6350: <hi rend="italic">India</hi> (<hi
                            rend="italic">Lord Privy Seal’s Mission</hi>) … April, 1942, p.
                        4.</note> These proposals are to be published simultaneously in India and in
                    London at 3 a.m. British Summer Time on Monday, March 30th, and arrangements are
                    being made by the British Information Services for its simultaneous release in
                    this country.</p>
                <p>Please treat these proposals as confidential until such time as they are
                    published.</p>
                <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Halifax</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>P. S. I enclose an additional copy and if you can get it, or the gist of it,
                        to the President before publication, I would be grateful if you would.
                        H.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
